    "description": "A fully synthetic azo dye derived from petroleum-based aromatic compounds (historically coal tar). Produces strawberry-red colour. One of the 'Southampton Six' colours linked to hyperactivity in children."
  },
  "manufacturing": {
    "method": "diazotization and azo coupling",
    "description": "Naphthionic acid (1-amino-4-naphthalenesulfonic acid) is diazotized using sodium nitrite in hydrochloric acid at 0-5°C. The resulting diazonium salt couples with G-acid (2-naphthol-6,8-disulfonic acid) in alkaline medium (pH 9-10) via electrophilic aromatic substitution. The product is purified, salted out with sodium chloride, and converted to the trisodium salt form."
  },
